org.openimaj.util.list

Class AbstractStreamBackedList<T extends Readable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.AbstractSequentialList<T>
          • org.openimaj.util.list.AbstractStreamBackedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of object which can be read by this list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>, RandomisableList<T>

    public abstract class AbstractStreamBackedList<T extends Readable>
extends AbstractSequentialList<T>
implements RandomisableList<T>
    A list of records that can be consumed from a stream. Records can only be read in order and concurrent access is a really bad idea. Once a list is exhausted by consuming all it's elements it cannot be reused. The stream will be closed automatically when it is exhausted.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare
